Hint of this behavior was given by the dependence of plasma luminescence on the square of the current as recorded in reference25,26, but our measurement is the first to show a direct dependence of the plasma electron density on the discharge current in the AC regime. Therefore the design of specific current waveforms could enable one to precisely control the plasma density and reach even longer discharge lifetimes. Surprisingly the plasma resistance seems not to share the oscillatory behavior of electron density. Indeed discharge current is well fitted by a double damped sine:1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
