The oscillatory behavior observed with electron density is not shared by the neutral density profile (Fig. 2(d)). Indeed the underdense channel front keeps propagating in time, eventually reaching a 6 mm HWHM by 900 μs. Another precious information comes from the time evolution of the channel depth, here evaluated in terms of neutral molecule deficit over the whole discharge by integrating the density profile:6\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
